    Mission Statement and Research Program Plans for the Southern Plains
                           Range Research Station

       The Southern Plains Range Research Station (SPRRS) mission is to
   develop sustainable production practices through improved management of
   energy flow, nutrient cycling, and hydrologic dynamics for Southern
   Plains rangeland and associated agricultural ecosystems.

      An overview of the Range Research strategy of the USDA-ARS: A Vision
   for Rangeland Research


